    {"id": 2, "statement": "Bob Dylan and the Beatles are mentioned as artists who challenged authority through music.", "answer": true, "evidence": "Artists including Bob Dylan, the Beatles, Janis Joplin, and Jimi Hendrix used their songs to challenge authority and celebrate freedom."},
    {"id": 3, "statement": "Andy Warhol was a Beat writer known for breaking with conventional narrative forms.", "answer": false, "evidence": "Warhol led the Pop Art movement in visual art. Beat writers such as Jack Kerouac were a separate group."},
